{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:43.034941+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 6ebc2af79b91200a02d42f2ee044c6196927972f)", "id": "lc_cdb83161-c8af-4ec1-8cf9-a47932f053c6"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import React, { useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport { useNavigate } from \"react-router-dom\";\nimport { auth } from \"../../config/firebase\";\n\nconst AuthChecker = ({ children }) => {\n  const navigate = useNavigate();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!auth.currentUser) {\n      navigate(\"/login\");\n    }\n  }, []); // eslint-disable-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps\n\n  return <>{children}</>;\n};\n\nexport default AuthChecker;\n", "id": "lc_32711e43-3a02-4ae8-8167-596922de3081"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "af1264dc-cb75-4709-9ed8-4613e0fe8e20", "tool_call_id": "call_00_Hr8bHfPJOtMUUnL06NYv3826", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:50.101436+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Routing Configuration\n\nThe app uses **React Router v6** with a `BrowserRouter` wrapping a `<Routes>` block (see `src/App.js`). The route definitions are stored declaratively in **`src/config/routes.js`** as an array of objects, each with four fields:\n\n- `path` – the URL path  \n- `component` – the React component to render  \n- `name` – a human-readable label  \n- `protected` – a boolean that controls whether the route requires authentication  \n\nIn `App.js` the array is mapped to `<Route>` elements. When `route.protected` is `true`, the component is wrapped with `<AuthChecker>`; otherwise it is rendered directly.\n\n---\n\n## Routes defined\n\n| Path       | Component | `protected` | Accessibility     |\n|------------|-----------|-------------|-------------------|\n| `\"\"` (root) | `Home`    | `true`      | **Requires authentication** |\n| `/login`   | `Login`   | `false`     | **Public**         |\n\n---\n\n## How authentication enforcement works\n\nThe `AuthChecker` component (`src/components/auth/AuthChecker.js`) checks `auth.currentUser` (from Firebase) inside a `useEffect`. If no user is logged in, it navigates to `/login`. This wrapper is applied at the route level, so any route marked `protected: true` is guarded automatically.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n- **Protected route (requires auth):** `\"/\"` (Home page)  \n- **Public route (no auth needed):** `\"/login\"` (Login screen)  \n\nThe entire mechanism is driven by the `protected` property in the route configuration object in `src/config/routes.js`, combined with the conditional `<AuthChecker>` wrapper in `App.js`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 602, "prompt_tokens": 6143, "total_tokens": 6745, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 226, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 5888}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 5888, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 255}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "3f5079f8-f5c6-41b6-b874-2a42922e4ea4", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3e6-f61b-70e0-84f7-69f05990aa87-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6143, "output_tokens": 602, "total_tokens": 6745, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 5888}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 226}}}}]}}}
